We were interested in the fold-change of each D. virilis gene across the four libraries, rather than the absolute abundance of any particular gene. Therefore, after mapping and gene quantification, we normalized the abundance Aij of every gene i across the j = 4 libraries by a weighted average of the quantity Qj of D. virilis in library j, as show in Eq. (2). Thus, within a given gene, a linear fit of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
